holiday inn is a 1942 american musical film directed by mark sandrich and starring bing crosby and fred astaire . with music by irving berlin , the composer wrote twelve songs specifically for the film , the best known being " white christmas . " the film features the complete reuse of " easter parade , " written by berlin for the 1933 broadway revue as thousands cheer . the film 's choreography was by danny dare . the film received a 1943 academy award for best original song ( irving berlin for " white christmas " ) , as well as academy award nominations for best score ( robert emmett dolan ) and best original story ( irving berlin ) .